997
01:20:48,566 --> 01:20:51,436
With their metabolic rates,
it'll kill them fast.

998
01:20:54,405 --> 01:20:56,896
Selenium. How much do we need?

999
01:21:00,244 --> 01:21:02,913
Five hundred gallons should do it.

1000
01:21:03,163 --> 01:21:04,823
Five hundred gallons?

1001
01:21:06,459 --> 01:21:10,326
l hate to be a buzzkill,
but where will we get that at 2:00 a.m.?

1002
01:21:10,420 --> 01:21:11,998
No problem.

1003
01:21:12,256 --> 01:21:13,750
We can get that.

1004
01:21:17,886 --> 01:21:19,381
Head & Shoulders.

1005
01:21:19,596 --> 01:21:21,007
The dandruff shampoo?

1006
01:21:21,098 --> 01:21:24,716
Yeah, that's the stuff.
The active ingredient is selenium sulphide.

1007
01:21:28,438 --> 01:21:30,846
How do you know that?
You don't know anything.

1008
01:21:30,941 --> 01:21:34,356
Haven't you noticed
how shiny and flake-free our hair is?

1009
01:21:38,782 --> 01:21:41,948
Okay, this is the best idea we got.

1010
01:21:42,285 --> 01:21:44,776
Let's give it a shot. come on.

1011
01:21:45,246 --> 01:21:48,033
We'll get the troops together.
We're getting shampoo!

1012
01:21:48,124 --> 01:21:49,951
l have the perfect vehicle.

1013
01:21:50,042 --> 01:21:53,874
Good! Donalds, you just got your A's.

1014
01:22:03,389 --> 01:22:04,587
Almost full.

1015
01:22:09,478 --> 01:22:13,475
There's something l should tell you,
but l don't know exactly how.

1016
01:22:14,650 --> 01:22:19,145
Just say it. We're adults and we're
about to die a horrible death soon anyway.

1017
01:22:21,656 --> 01:22:23,981
l would have rocked your world.

1018
01:22:29,372 --> 01:22:31,910
-You already have.
-All full.

1019
01:22:31,999 --> 01:22:34,158
Battle stations!

1020
01:22:37,505 --> 01:22:39,830
can we continue this discussion later?

1021
01:22:41,759 --> 01:22:43,087
Let's do this!

1022
01:22:45,012 --> 01:22:46,720
Let's shampoo us some aliens!

1023
01:23:06,784 --> 01:23:08,443
Lots of soldiers around.

1024
01:23:14,665 --> 01:23:19,708
There's an old mine half a click south.
We can sneak into the cave through there.

1025
01:23:19,921 --> 01:23:22,246
''Half a click''? What are you, in Vietnam?

1026
01:23:22,340 --> 01:23:25,294
Hey, I'm digging this. Work with me.

1027
01:23:44,820 --> 01:23:47,572
It's over here! It's right here!

1028
01:23:50,951 --> 01:23:52,824
-Are you okay?
-I'm good.

1029
01:23:54,579 --> 01:23:55,742
Let's go!

1030
01:23:56,081 --> 01:23:57,326
Let's do this.

1031
01:23:58,541 --> 01:24:00,581
You sure this leads to the main cavern?

1032
01:24:00,669 --> 01:24:03,421
It'll lead somewhere.
Geology's not an exact science.

1033
01:24:06,925 --> 01:24:08,585
Where are you?

1034
01:24:09,594 --> 01:24:11,551
Where are you, my little aliens?

1035
01:24:12,639 --> 01:24:14,133
Show yourself.

1036
01:24:24,525 --> 01:24:26,269
Warm to the touch.

1037
01:24:30,114 --> 01:24:31,359
Highly acidic.

1038
01:24:31,949 --> 01:24:35,115
We've no time for you
to act like you know what you're doing.

1039
01:24:35,202 --> 01:24:36,577
What happened to the respect?

1040
01:24:36,662 --> 01:24:39,200
Woodman's going at noon.
We have to hurry.

1041
01:24:42,876 --> 01:24:45,877
-Good. Are the troops in place?
-Ahead of schedule.

1042
01:24:45,963 --> 01:24:47,955
Excellent. We can go early.

1043
01:24:48,965 --> 01:24:51,801
Oh, no. What is he doing here?

1044
01:24:54,971 --> 01:24:56,299
Governor Lewis.

1045
01:24:56,556 --> 01:24:59,474
l don't see anything burning.
Where are all the explosions?

1046
01:24:59,685 --> 01:25:03,135
We're just getting underway.
l didn't know you were coming to watch.

1047
01:25:03,229 --> 01:25:05,637
Well, better make it a good one, Sergeant.

1048
01:25:05,982 --> 01:25:07,310
That's General.

1049
01:25:07,566 --> 01:25:10,521
Not if you screw this up.
Keeping my chair warm for me?

1050
01:25:11,905 --> 01:25:13,066
Thank you.

1051
01:25:13,989 --> 01:25:16,694
I'll take a pair of spy glasses
and a hot chocolate.

1052
01:25:16,784 --> 01:25:18,195
Give me the hose.

1053
01:25:18,827 --> 01:25:23,288
Get up top. When l give the signal,
start pumping the selenium.

1054
01:25:23,457 --> 01:25:24,868
Got it.

1055
01:25:44,602 --> 01:25:47,094
We'll spray all around the meteor...

1056
01:25:47,439 --> 01:25:50,011
...then get out of here as fast as we can.

1057
01:25:53,361 --> 01:25:55,354
Blue monkey!

1058
01:25:57,531 --> 01:25:59,857
Wayne, charge the line now!

1059
01:26:09,710 --> 01:26:11,169
That's the napalm!

1060
01:26:11,629 --> 01:26:13,123
Woodman went early.

1061
01:26:23,724 --> 01:26:25,432
Bad!

1062
01:26:25,976 --> 01:26:27,518
Wayne, come on!

1063
01:26:30,564 --> 01:26:31,892
I'm out.

1064
01:26:39,740 --> 01:26:41,482
We've got to go!

1065
01:26:44,244 --> 01:26:47,743
Go! Faster! Get up there!

1066
01:26:49,999 --> 01:26:51,992
Run for your life!

1067
01:26:57,423 --> 01:27:01,005
Quite a bonfire we've got.
Should have brought some wieners.

1068
01:27:01,343 --> 01:27:02,838
That can be arranged.

1069
01:27:02,928 --> 01:27:06,261
-First reports are excellent, sir.
-Very good.

1070
01:27:09,351 --> 01:27:11,059
Keep it together, Wayne.

1071
01:27:12,938 --> 01:27:14,101
Oh, my God.

1072
01:27:22,030 --> 01:27:23,441
What's happening?

1073
01:27:25,033 --> 01:27:26,942
-It's coming!
-What's coming?

1074
01:27:28,996 --> 01:27:29,944
Get the hell out of here!

1075
01:27:31,789 --> 01:27:34,826
-Great flaming whore balls!
-General, look!

1076
01:27:50,057 --> 01:27:51,386
Hurry!

1077
01:27:51,892 --> 01:27:53,766
-Drive!
-Go!

1078
01:27:55,020 --> 01:27:56,680
All right!

1079
01:28:48,948 --> 01:28:50,940
Fall back!

1080
01:28:55,996 --> 01:28:57,905
What the hell is that thing?

1081
01:28:58,164 --> 01:29:02,661
The napalm forced an evolutionary
response, like the match in the petri dish.

1082
01:29:03,836 --> 01:29:05,247
That's evolution?

1083
01:29:05,505 --> 01:29:09,751
Survival of the fittest. Often,
the simplest organism is the strongest.

1084
01:29:10,093 --> 01:29:11,920
Guys? It's freaking out!

1085
01:29:12,178 --> 01:29:15,345
It's starting to have
some sort of spaz attack.

1086
01:29:16,515 --> 01:29:19,007
That's not spazzing out.

1087
01:29:20,353 --> 01:29:22,097
It's getting ready to divide.

1088
01:29:26,693 --> 01:29:28,021
Mitosis.

1089
01:29:28,777 --> 01:29:31,862
Wait. There's going to be more
of these things?

1090
01:29:32,198 --> 01:29:35,032
-A lot more.
-Its cycle is starting again.

1091
01:29:35,868 --> 01:29:39,451
It will go on growing and doubling
until it takes over.

1092
01:29:40,373 --> 01:29:42,365
But we were here first.

1093
01:29:44,543 --> 01:29:48,243
So that Head & Shoulders idea.
Is that still the plan?

1094
01:29:52,551 --> 01:29:53,713
I'm driving.

1095
01:29:53,801 --> 01:29:57,634
So what if he's on Air Force One?
It has phones. I've seen them!

1096
01:29:57,723 --> 01:29:59,964
l don't think this can wait an hour.

1097
01:30:01,809 --> 01:30:04,217
What's that fire truck doing out there?

1098
01:30:20,619 --> 01:30:21,818
Mama.

1099
01:30:29,253 --> 01:30:30,912
can you believe this?

1100
01:30:31,254 --> 01:30:33,828
We have to find a point of attack.

1101
01:30:38,762 --> 01:30:40,090
There!

1102
01:30:48,939 --> 01:30:50,267
Nasty!

1103
01:30:50,606 --> 01:30:52,932
Allison, stop. Right here.

1104
01:30:55,945 --> 01:30:57,605
Here we go!

1105
01:30:58,281 --> 01:30:59,941
Get the ladder up!

1106
01:31:01,534 --> 01:31:03,443
Feed me the hose, Deke.

1107
01:31:04,036 --> 01:31:06,278
-What are you doing?
-Going up top.

1108
01:31:06,623 --> 01:31:09,623
Not before me.
l got a major score to settle.

1109
01:31:09,959 --> 01:31:11,619
Go, go, go!

1110
01:31:27,809 --> 01:31:31,309
We don't have much time, guys! Hurry!

1111
01:31:37,152 --> 01:31:39,145
-Left!
-Left!

1112
01:31:39,487 --> 01:31:42,322
Got it.
l haven't had much practice with this.

1113
01:31:45,993 --> 01:31:48,152
Stop!

1114
01:31:51,291 --> 01:31:54,291
-What's going on?
-l don't know, but it's getting bigger.

1115
01:31:54,377 --> 01:31:57,212
What are they doing with that ladder?

1116
01:31:58,922 --> 01:32:02,090
Looks like they're getting ready
to administer a jumbo enema.

1117
01:32:03,177 --> 01:32:05,668
We got one shot. Let's do this.

1118
01:32:06,347 --> 01:32:09,016
It's payback time!

1119
01:32:13,854 --> 01:32:15,348
Keep it in there!

1120
01:32:15,689 --> 01:32:17,681
What's it look like I'm doing?

1121
01:32:19,192 --> 01:32:21,019
It's working!

1122
01:32:26,950 --> 01:32:28,279
Shit!

1123
01:32:30,453 --> 01:32:31,698
What the hell?

1124
01:32:31,871 --> 01:32:34,197
Oh, my God!

1125
01:32:34,374 --> 01:32:36,947
Give me back my friend, you big sphincter!

1126
01:32:37,710 --> 01:32:39,121
She's going to blow!

1127
01:32:39,295 --> 01:32:40,540
Stop kicking!

1128
01:32:40,630 --> 01:32:42,373
It's horrible in here!

1129
01:32:42,715 --> 01:32:45,206
-l got you!
-Help me!

1130
01:32:45,551 --> 01:32:48,220
Hold me, Ira! Don't let me go!

1131
01:32:52,016 --> 01:32:54,720
We have to get out of here!
This thing's going to blow!

1132
01:32:55,018 --> 01:32:57,426
You cannot imagine what l saw in there!

1133
01:32:57,730 --> 01:32:59,058
Hurry up, guys!

1134
01:32:59,273 --> 01:33:03,105
Ira! Don't you ever tell anyone
where I've been!

1135
01:33:03,944 --> 01:33:05,023
Dear Lord.

1136
01:33:10,784 --> 01:33:12,444
Uh-oh. Time to go.

1137
01:33:15,205 --> 01:33:16,450
Go!

1138
01:33:39,937 --> 01:33:41,266
We did it!

1139
01:34:16,848 --> 01:34:21,594
Here we go, sir. Just relax
and we'll have you as good as new.

1140
01:34:22,103 --> 01:34:26,101
l am happy to report
that all remaining traces...

1141
01:34:26,191 --> 01:34:28,515
...of the alien menace
have been eradicated...

1142
01:34:28,609 --> 01:34:31,943
...using the selenium shampoo formula
developed right here.

1143
01:34:32,029 --> 01:34:36,192
Let me introduce our civilian scientist
heroes and their team...

1144
01:34:36,450 --> 01:34:41,112
...the best the great state of Arizona
has been privileged to produce.

1145
01:34:44,875 --> 01:34:49,869
So this is your moment. You wouldn't
want to miss this for anything.

1146
01:34:50,714 --> 01:34:55,210
Firstly, l would like you all
to meet Wayne Gray.

1147
01:34:56,053 --> 01:35:00,050
As of today, a fully credentialed fire-fighter.

1148
01:35:00,390 --> 01:35:02,217
l spoke to the chief.

1149
01:35:02,726 --> 01:35:04,137
Thanks, Governor.

1150
01:35:07,730 --> 01:35:09,225
Now, our next hero...

1151
01:35:09,315 --> 01:35:12,102
...Professor Harry Block, noted geologist...

1152
01:35:12,443 --> 01:35:15,480
...and winningest coach
in north Arizona women's volleyball.

1153
01:35:15,572 --> 01:35:17,481
l appreciate that, Governor.

1154
01:35:17,741 --> 01:35:20,860
First, l thank God.
With Him, all things are possible.

1155
01:35:21,077 --> 01:35:24,908
We just played tough defence,
took it one alien at a time...

1156
01:35:24,997 --> 01:35:27,073
...and came away with the big W.

1157
01:35:32,921 --> 01:35:34,167
And finally...

1158
01:35:35,091 --> 01:35:37,759
...Doctors Ira Kane and Allison Reed...

1159
01:35:38,093 --> 01:35:42,755
...whose tireless efforts, research,
and academic findings led to the....

1160
01:35:44,099 --> 01:35:46,768
l think he's giving her
a bit of the Kane Madness.

1161
01:36:01,366 --> 01:36:04,366
Wow! Fighting the alien menace
can be tough work.

1162
01:36:04,702 --> 01:36:07,538
So is keeping your hair clean,
shiny and dandruff-free.

1163
01:36:07,664 --> 01:36:10,664
So it is a good thing that we always keep a healthy supply of...

1164
01:36:11,000 --> 01:36:13,159
...Head & Shoulders around the house.

